title: Braedan Baird’s CV
text:
Physicist, Mathematician, Cambridge professor.

bbaird77@byui.edu



Studying at BYU-I.



Experienced in MS Office Suite
Familiar with both PC & Mac Formats
Experienced with the Adobe Creative Suite
Experienced with RStudio and VS Code Programs
Certified with the SolidWorks CAD Program
Experienced with Lathes, Drill Presses & Welding
Proficient with General Mechanical & Hand Tools




Writing, Math, Science, Computer Software, and Computer Hardware.




Brigham Young University Idaho Attending: 2018, 2021 – Current, Rexburg, ID Conestoga Valley Senior High School
Graduated: 2017, Lancaster, PA



Crew Member, McDonald’s, Rexburg, ID
Oct 2021 – Dec 2022, Sep 2023 - Current * Maintained clean, sanitized, and well-organized food preparation zones and prepared cooking supplies, ingredients, and workstations during opening and closing procedures. * Promoted general customer loyalty and provided customer service. * Processed payments and counted change to complete transactions.
Delivery Associate, Amazon, Mount Joy, PA January 2023 – Sep 2023 * Lifted and moved packages weighing up to 50 lbs. and efficiently loaded and safely drove delivery vehicle. * Navigated surrounding areas and delivered packages safely and efficiently. * Maintained excellent attendance record, consistently arriving at work on time. * Met and exceeded assigned production standards for quality and quotas.
Teacher Assistant, Brigham Young University Idaho, Rexburg, ID Oct 2021 – May 2022 * Assisted with grading assignments and promptly returning them to students. * Assisted students with concepts and ideas necessary for their growth and overall success in the course. * Provided additional help and assistance to individual students to overcome difficulties in comprehension and mastery.
